This is an In-Depth look into all the functionalities of Motorsport Ultimate.
Artiick Note: OBVIOUSLY In-Game you won't see all the "444" you'll see here. That's just the default number I used for texts to align stuff properly.
*The Images contained here may not reflect what the Overlays look like at a given time if they've been updated/changed.
Always refer on the latest Preview Screenshots (currently up to date to 1.5.0).
Timing Sheet:
Starting the race you will only see displayed your current laptime
After you completed your 1st lap, the Predicted laptime will also show up
When you cross Start/Finish, you'll see for 3 seconds your last laptime and the split to best
Note: If you are in a Timed Race Event, it'll take 1 completed lap for the Overlay to swap to the "Timed Race mode".
Delta Bar:
During your 1st of the race only the "Track Limit Indicator" will show up. The element will only be a fancy ui indicator.
It'll change to Yellow or Red depending on how close you are to Track Limis
After you completed your 1st lap, the Delta Bar will also show up. Text color will change accordingly
Note: The Delta is self-relying as it does all the necessary calcualtions on its own. This may cause slight discrepancies based on your System Latency
Race Information:
The element will immediately show up at Race Start
When you cross Start/Fin, you'll see for 3 seconds your Distance Driven (in big).
Lap History:
At Race Start and you'll only see displayed your current laptime
After you complete your laps you'll start to see them as they start appearing. Additionally there will be displayed your Overall Average laptime.
When you cross Start/Finish, for 3 seconds the AVG will change to green and display the "Possible best average" (excludes pitstops, lap 1 etc)
When you cross Start/Finish, if you set a new PB the Element background, and text color will change accordingly
When you cross Start/Finish, if your previous lap was within a set threshold of your PB, it will turn green for 3 seconds, indicating it was a Good Lap
When you cross Start/Finish, if your previous lap was slower then a set threshold of your PB, it will turn red for 3 seconds, indicating it was a Bad Lap
Threshold Set: It has been arbitrarily set at +100.125% of the Best Laptime. It's a tight margin but since it's static it'll expand the longer a laptime is.
This is by design as it's supposed to be a simple indicator of "Oh ok, lap was good/bad".
Note 2: Lap-History-v1c will only change the background color
Vehicle telemetry:
The outer border or the tires will indicate your tire slip. Color will gradually change from white to
Red = The tire is sliding.
The tire itself + the text will indicate your Tire Temperature. Both Text and Tire will change color in unison following a color table*.
These bars will indicate the suspension compression. Color & height will gradually increase from white to
Red = The spring is fully compressed/bottomed out.
These red bars will turn on and flash white/red if your wheel is making contact with kerb & kerb-type surfaces.
These blue bars will turn on and flash white/blue if your wheel is making contact with puddles when its raining.
Color Table for Tire Temps
Fuel Information:
NOTE: Updated to show 2 decimals for enhanced precision.
At Race Start and you'll only see displayed your current fuel % (the fuel bar will follow it accordingly)
After you completed your 1st lap, Remaining Laps Estimate and Average Fuel Consumption will appear
The fuel bar will turn Yellow once you have 20% fuel left. And then smoothly change to red
It'll then be fully Red once you have <= 5% fuel left
Color change Fuel Bar
Note: Remaining Laps Estimate will take 2-3 laps to return pin-point accurate values
Tire Wear:
At Race Start and you'll only see displayed your tire wear. The tire itself + text will change color* based on the wear for easier identification.
Color Table for Tire Wear
Every time you cross Start/Finish, for 3 seconds, you'll see displayed your last lap Tire Consumption instead of the total Current Tire Wear
After 2 completed laps your Average Tire Wear x Lap will also appear. These will indicate how much tire (in%) you are currently using per lap
Pit Stop Related: Time Lost - Predicted Pit Stop - Mini Alert
NOTE: The Time Lost (will show up after 1 lap) and Alert (will show up at the lap you're predicted to pit and go away when you pit)
are static elements so I'll just cover the main Predicted Stop UI functions.
The element will show up after 1 lap and will start displaying the amount of laps left to when it predicts your next pit stop is.
As you drive each lap it'll get more precise and change the icon to one of 3 states (Tires, Refuel or Both) to indicate you what needs to be done in Pits.
When you are predicted to stop the next lap, the "NEXT LAP" text will start fading between that Dark Yellow to a Pure Bright Yellow, for ease of visibility.
When you're predicted to stop in this lap the background element color will start alternating between a Black and Red tint (every 3s). Also here is when the "Mini Alert" will show up on the right side of your screen
If you don't stop at the predicted point and Extend your stint. The element will update accordingly and show you a specific UI indicating how many laps you've extended the stint for. The outline will flash brighter every 3s.
Mini Sectors
During the first lap of the race you'll only see the reduced bar, and the elements will only color purple as the formulas gather the initial data and Mini Sector Timings.
From lap 2 of the race, the full element will appear and your Optimal Laptime will also be calculated. Each small rectangle will be correctly colored:
If you went faster in that Mini Sector,
If it's about equal,
If you went slower than the +100.125%.
Each time you cross Start/Fin, you'll see your previous lap Micro Sec. (for 3s), and a colored outline will flash with color:
If you set a new PB,
If your previous lap was within that +100.125% of PB,
If your previous lap was slower than the +100.125% of pb,
If your previous lap was dirty.
Position Arrows
It'll simply indicate you how many positions you gained/lost during the race, in real time.
Race Notifications
The Mini Race Notifications will appear in the Top Right corner of your screen (for tires and fuel) if/when you have:
5 laps of Fuel Left or Minor Tire Wear ( Rectangle, Text),
3 laps of Fuel Left or Moderate Tire Wear ( Rectangle, Text),
1 laps of Fuel Left or Severe Tire Wear ( Rectangle, Text).
Tachometer (Manual):
Base Elements:
  1. Shift Lights
  2. RPM Gauge
  3. RPM Markers (every 1000 RPM)
  4. (Fully colored Red) Over Rev Limit Range
    (Faded to Red) Approaching Rev Limit
  5. Steer Input (Right/Left) and Steer Center Icon
  6. Brake Input
  7. Throttle Input
  8. Simple x1000 Graphical marker
  9. (Number) Your current car PI
    (Colored letter) Your current car class
  10. An F1-Style RPM Marker that will follow the Gauge and stop briefly at the highest point
  11. (Hidden) Upshift Beep played at Shiftpoint
Details:
1a. Will light up at 85% of the Shiftpoint you set
1b. Will light up at 88% of the Shiftpoint you set
1c. Will light up at 91% of the Shiftpoint you set
1d. Will light up at 94% of the Shiftpoint you set
1e. Will light up at 97% of the Shiftpoint you set
All. They will all turn Red and start flashing/blinking every 100ms when you are or over your Shiftpoint
2. Your RPM Gauge will turn Red when you reach or are over your set Shiftpoint.
It will then start flashing White/Red when you're well above it and you're reaching close to your Rev Limit
4. Both the Red colored range and the fade will automatically set correctly based on the Rev Limit you set.
9. The Class Letter will be correctly colored following the game color scheme: E, D, C, B, A, S, R, P, X.
Main Dial:
  1. Gearing
  2. Current Speed (KMH)
  3. Lateral G's Meter
  4. Upshift Arrow Indicator
Details:
1a. Current Gear indicator. Will turn the same way the RPM Gauge does.
1b. Previous Gear indicator
1c. Next Gear indicator
Note: When driving new cars for the first time ever, 1c will work properly only after your cycled through the entire gears (thank forza UDP for that since it doesn't actually tell how many gears the car has)
2a. Current Speed (MPH or KPH depending on your local SimHub settings)
4. The Upshift arrow will only show up after you reach or are over your set Shiftpoint. It's a simple graphical indicator
Info Mini-Dial:
  1. Current Engine RPM
  2. Current Torque produced by Engine
  3. Current Power produced by Engine
  4. Boost pressure, Positive and Negative boost gauge bars
  5. Input Traces
Details:
4. The element won't show up in NA cars
The Boost gauge bars will follow your current engine boost. In both + pressure (Boost) and - pressure (Vacuum)
5. Your input traces (Throttle, Brake, Steer, Clutch, E-Brake) will stay containted and show up within the faint Cyan colored box

Base Elements:
  1. Shift Lights
  2. RPM Gauge
  3. RPM Markers (every 1000 RPM)
  4. (Fully colored Red) Over Rev Limit Range
    (Faded to Red) Approaching Rev Limit

  10. An F1-Style RPM Marker that will follow the Gauge and stop briefly at the highest point
  11. (Hidden) Upshift Beep played at 95% of Rev limit
Details:
1a. Will light up at 82.5% of the Automated Rev Limit
1b. Will light up at 85% of the Automated Rev Limit
1c. Will light up at 87.5% of the Automated Rev Limit
1d. Will light up at 90% of the Automated Rev Limit
1e. Will light up at 92.5% of the Automated Rev Limit
All. They will all turn Red and start flashing/blinking every 100ms when you are or over 95% of the Automated Rev Limit
2. Your RPM Gauge will turn Red when you reach or are over 95% of the Automated Rev Limit.
4. Both the Red colored range and the fade will automatically set correctly based on the Automated Rev Limit
9. The Class Letter will be correctly colored following the game color scheme: E, D, C, B, A, S, R, P, X.
